thread.title: TV | The Kennedys

author: Jason Brennan
title: TV | The Kennedys
text: This new comedy set in the 70s is loosely based on the early writer Emma Kennedy, a Star Wars-obsessed 10-year-old tomboy. The first episode sees Emma's aspirationally minded mother determined to be the first person on their street to throw a dinner party. Of course all the neighbours arrive over for "a night they won't remember". We'll take a massive stab in the dark and guess that it all goes a bit pear-shaped, how fresh. But whether the plot is obvious of not, we're definitely tuning in to give it a go, mainly because Katherine Parkinson is starring, and she's always hilarious.
